description:
src/lib.rs:124 'pub fn from_uri(uri: &str) -> Result<Self, SecretError>'. Clippy::missing_errors_doc (pedantic) warns that public functions returning Result should document the error conditions in a '# Errors' rustdoc section.

The function does enumerate errors implicitly in the body (InvalidUri for various URI shape problems, Unavailable for missing GCP_ACCESS_TOKEN), but rustdoc readers benefit from a structured # Errors block:

  /// # Errors
  ///
  /// Returns [SecretError::InvalidUri] if:
  ///   - the URI does not have backend 'gcp-sm'
  ///   - the path is not '<project>/<secret>'
  ///   - any of project, secret, version contain characters outside [A-Za-z0-9_-]
  ///   - ?version= is empty
  ///
  /// Returns [SecretError::Unavailable] if GCP_ACCESS_TOKEN is not set in the environment.

Engineering basis: a public API used by URI strings is exactly the audience that benefits from a clear error matrix at rustdoc time. The body of the function is the source of truth, but enumerating in docs avoids forcing readers to read the implementation.
